Iâ€™m not pushing for application/xhtml+xml (which has its own merits and issues). As I see it, if you can serve &lt;hr&gt; as text/html, you should also be able to serve &lt;hr/&gt; as text/html.<br /><br />My point is that if the new standard allows &lt;hr/&gt; only, then at least the tags are xhtml ready, existing editors and parsers will be happy, and the syntax will be simplified by not offering unnecessary alternatives. Software that generates HTML will easily output the necessary tags (and probably already does), and hand coding the syntax is not a lot of extra effort.<br /><br />Mark<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1037">manngo</a> — Tue Mar 23, 2010 10:22 am</p><hr />
